Project 1a
Files included:
1. lab1a.c: the source file
2. Makefile: used to build program, clean files and generate tarball
3. README: brief introduction of the files and functions

The function can be run in the shell by:
$ gcc -g -o lab1a lab1a.c
$ ./lab1a [--shell]

Also, you can use Makefile to compile, check and generate tarball. The corresponding codes are:
 
>> make default : compile the resource file

>> make clean : remove all the files generated by check

>> make dist : build the distribution tarball

Sources of code:

1. pipe: http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/pipe.2.html
2. termios: http://www.cs.uleth.ca/~holzmann/C/system/ttyraw.c
3. poll: https://linux.die.net/man/3/poll
4. dup2: http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/dup.2.html
5. execvp: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27541910/how-to-use-execvp
6. waitpid: https://linux.die.net/man/2/waitpid